# Opportunity.ai - Cursor Rules

## Quick Reference

This file provides quick access to key project information for Cursor AI.

## Project Vision

Opportunity.ai is an AI-assisted job search and application management platform that helps tech professionals discover jobs, tailor applications, and track their pipeline across multiple countries.

**Core Features:**
- AI-Powered Job Discovery with ranking
- Tailored Application Materials (CV, cover letter, outreach)
- Job Application Pipeline Tracking
- Personalized Insights & Skill Guidance
- User Control & Privacy (GDPR compliant)

**See:** [VISION.md](VISION.md) for full vision

## Key Rules Reference

**Agent Operating System:** [.cursor/rules/00-operating-system.md](.cursor/rules/00-operating-system.md)
- Always follow work loop: clarify → plan → implement → verify → summarize
- Run checks: `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm test`
- Make incremental commits

**Product Scope:** [.cursor/rules/01-product-scope.md](.cursor/rules/01-product-scope.md)
- ✅ Allowed: Manual entry, CSV/JSON upload, official APIs
- ❌ Prohibited: LinkedIn scraping, auto-apply bots, bypassing protections

**Architecture:** [.cursor/rules/02-architecture.md](.cursor/rules/02-architecture.md)
- Next.js App Router with Server Components
- Service layer in `lib/services/`
- Data access in `lib/db/queries/`
- AI calls server-side only

**Coding Standards:** [.cursor/rules/03-coding-standards.md](.cursor/rules/03-coding-standards.md)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Zod for runtime validation
- Small functions, clear names
- JSDoc for non-trivial functions

## Subagents

See [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) for subagent definitions:
- test-runner: Runs checks and fixes issues
- refactor-scout: Identifies simple refactors
- security-sentinel: Checks for security violations
- type-enforcer: Ensures TypeScript compliance
- migration-manager: Manages database migrations
- prompt-versioner: Versions AI prompts

